A doctor walks past a coronavirus information sign at Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital in Soweto. JOHANNESBURG - Over 27,000 healthcare workers in South Africa contracted COVID-19. While over 16,000 have fully recovered, 240 of them succumbed to the virus. READ: Over 300 workers at KZN hospital test positive for COVID-19 Health Minister Zweli Mkhize made the announcement on Thursday. Over 6,000 workers were from the private sector while more than 21,000 from the public sector. They include doctors, nurses, and others in the health sector. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.